nterview%20that%20aired%20Saturday.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EDuring%20the%20interview%2C%20he%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3Eput%20a%20simple%20riddle%20to%20OpenAI's%20GPT-4%2C%20which%20he%20said%20he%20used%20for%20his%20day-to-day%20tasks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSally%20has%20three%20brothers.%20Each%20of%20her%20brothers%20has%20two%20sisters.%20How%20many%20sisters%20does%20Sally%20have%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20answer%20is%20one%2C%20as%20Sally%20is%20one%20of%20the%20two%20sisters.%20But%20Hinton%20said%20GPT-4%20told%20him%20the%20answer%20was%20two.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20surprises%20me.%20It%20surprises%20me%20it%20still%20screws%20up%20on%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReflecting%20on%20the%20limits%20of%20current%20AI%2C%20he%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BIt's%20an%20expert%20at%20everything.%20It's%20not%20a%20very%20good%20expert%20at%20everything.%26quot%3B%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EHinton%20said%20he%20expected%20future%20models%20would%20do%20better.%20When%20asked%20if%20he%20thought%20GPT-5%20would%20get%20the%20riddle%20right%2C%20Hinton%20replied%2C%20%26quot%3BYeah%2C%20I%20suspect.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHinton's%20riddle%20didn't%20trip%20up%20every%20version%20of%20ChatGPT.%20After%20the%20interview%20aired%2C%20several%20people%20commented%20on%20social%20media%20that%20they%20tried%20the%20riddle%20on%20newer%20models%20%E2%80%94%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eincluding%20GPT-4o%20and%20GPT-4.1%20%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%94%3C%2Fstrong%3Eand%20said%20the%20AI%20got%20it%20right.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20first%20launched%20GPT-4%20in%202023%20as%20its%20flagship%20large%20language%20model.%20The%20model%20quickly%20became%20an%20industry%20benchmark%20for%20its%20ability%20to%20pass%20tough%20exams%20like%20the%20SAT%2C%20GRE%2C%20and%20bar%20exam.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business