me%20and%20give%20it%20to%20our%20kids%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fc375e6f-3d99-4112-a732-784d1d638ded%5C%22%3EI%20didn't%20think%20my%20husband's%20name%20was%20an%20option%20for%20me%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFast-forward%2012%20years%2C%20when%20we%20were%20finally%20getting%20hitched.%20A%20long%20courtship%20gave%20me%20lots%20of%20time%20to%20think%20about%20how%20only%20a%20handful%20of%20people%20in%20the%20world%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdivorce-change-back-last-name-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehave%20my%20last%20name%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Of%20that%20handful%2C%20I%20was%20the%20only%20one%20of%20the%20youngest%20generation%20planning%20to%20have%20children.%20Letting%20this%20last%20name%20die%20felt%20worse%20than%20my%20children%20potentially%20being%20on%20the%20receiving%20end%20of%20body%20gas%20taunts.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESeparately%2C%20my%20husband's%20last%20name%20lost%20some%20of%20its%20appeal.%20One%20night%20during%20our%20engagement%2C%20we%20were%20paying%20for%20our%20meal%20at%20our%20neighborhood%20Italian%20joint.%20When%20our%20server%20returned%20to%20our%20table%20with%20my%20husband's%20credit%20card%2C%20the%20server%20muttered%20my%20husband's%20last%20name%20with%20disgust%20and%20then%20pretended%20to%20spit%20on%20our%20receipt.%20We%20figured%20he%20was%20joking%2C%20but%20we%20didn't%20get%20the%20joke.%20Eventually%2C%20we%20learned%20my%20husband's%20last%20name%20meant%20he%20likely%20descended%20from%20Pontius%20Pilate%2C%20aka%20the%20Roman%20who%20demanded%20Jesus%20be%20crucified.%20Not%20the%20greatest%20branch%20of%20a%20family%20tree%2C%20nor%20a%20name%20I%20could%20continue%20to%20believe%20was%20categorically%20better%20than%20mine.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20my%20last%20name%20came%20from%20the%20German%20word%20for%20%26quot%3Bbathhouse.%26quot%3B%20Whether%20this%20meant%20my%20ancestors%20owned%20one%2C%20just%20frequented%20one%2C%20or%20used%20it%20to%20get%20clean%20or%20engage%20in%20more%20scandalous%20activities%2C%20this%20felt%20like%20a%20hilarious%20part%20of%20my%20identity%20I%20couldn't%20lose.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOur%20wedding%20came%20and%20went.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkept-married-name-after-my-divorce-its-my-kids-names-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20name%20stayed%20the%20same%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bf75d785-beca-47dd-8a71-24c873bf1177%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20had%20a%20harder%20time%20with%20last%20names%20than%20first%20names%20when%20it%20came%20to%20our%20kids%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFive%20years%20later%2C%20I%20was%20expecting%20our%20first%20child.%20It%20was%20tougher%20to%20choose%20his%20last%20name%20than%20his%20first.%20Around%20this%20time%2C%20we%20were%20also%20trying%20to%20sell%20our%20apartment%20and%20buy%20a%20house.%20Then%20we%20got%20some%20bad%20news%20from%20our%20real%20estate%20attorney%3A%20There%20was%20a%20lien%20on%20our%20apartment.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20were%20flummoxed%20when%20our%20lawyer%20gave%20us%20the%20unfamiliar%20name%20of%20the%20person%20who%20placed%20the%20lien.%20What%20was%20more%20confusing%3A%20The%20person%20lived%20nowhere%20near%20us.%20The%20one%20thing%20we%20knew%20was%20that%20until%20we%20removed%20the%20lien%2C%20no%20one%20was%20going%20to%20buy%20our%20apartment.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20turned%20out%20the%20lien%20was%20intended%20for%20some%20ne'er-do-well%20with%20my%20husband's%20exact%20same%20name%2C%20a%20guy%20who%20owed%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20a%20lot%20of%20money.%20A%20couple%20of%20affidavits%20later%2C%20the%20lien%20problem%20was%20resolved.%20But%20then%20I%20got%20a%20threatening%20social%20media%20message%20from%20a%20different%20creditor%20in%20upstate%20New%20York%2C%20convinced%20they'd%20found%20a%20way%20to%20get%20a%20note%20to%20the%20apparently%20hard-to-reach%20ne'er-do-well.%20I%20told%20the%20messenger%20they%20had%20the%20wrong%20guy.%20He%20didn't%20apologize%2C%20but%20he%20never%20contacted%20me%20again.%20With%20my%20almost-unique%20last%20name%2C%20my%20kids%20would%20never%20be%20the%20wrong%20guy.%20That%20felt%20like%20a%20nice%20gift%20to%20pass%20down.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20much%20back-and-forth%2C%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20decided%20to%20hyphenate%20our%20kids'%20last%20names.%20This%20ensured%20they%20would%20each%20be%20the%20one%20and%20only%2C%20impossible%20to%20confuse%20with%20any%20other%20individual.%20It%20also%20guaranteed%20rude%20comments%3A%20%26quot%3BHow%20are%20they%20going%20to%20be%20able%20to%20spell%20all%20that%3F%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BDid%20you%20name%20them%20that%20on%20purpose%3F%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20especially%20astute%2C%20%26quot%3BWow%2C%20that's%20a%20long%20name.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDespite%20those%20real%20rude%20comments%20and%20some%20relatives%20who%20refuse%20to%20acknowledge%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblended-last-names-after-marriage-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eboth%20parts%20of%20their%20names%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20we're%20happy%20with%20our%20decision.%20Our%20kids%2C%20now%207%20and%2010%2C%20have%20fewer%20issues%20with%20their%20long%20name%20than%20I%20did%20with%20my%20short%20one.%20We%20live%20in%20a%20much%20more%20diverse%20area%20than%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20grew%20up%20in%2C%20so%20there%20are%20all%20kinds%20of%20names%20here%2C%20even%20other%20hyphenated%20ones.%20We%20talk%20all%20the%20time%20about%20how%20cool%20it%20is%20that%20there's%20no%20one%20else%20out%20there%20with%20their%20n