2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJoe%20Biden%20has%20been%20diagnosed%20with%20%26quot%3Baggressive%26quot%3B%20prostate%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20has%20spread%20to%20his%20bones%2C%20after%20experiencing%20urinary%20symptoms%2C%20his%20private%20office%20said%20on%20Sunday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhip-pain-prostate-cancer-sign-symptoms-chiropractor-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EProstate%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20the%20second-deadliest%20form%20of%20cancer%20in%20men%20in%20the%20US%2C%20after%20lung%20cancer%2C%20and%20affects%20the%20gland%20that%20sits%20beneath%20the%20bladder%20and%20in%20front%20of%20the%20rectum%20in%20males.%20About%20one%20in%20eight%20men%20will%20get%20prostate%20cancer%2C%20but%20most%20will%20not%20die%20of%20the%20disease%2C%20according%20to%20the%20American%20Cancer%20Society.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%20It%20is%20a%20somewhat%20paradoxical%20disease%3A%20when%20caught%20early%2C%20it%20is%20often%20curable%20%E2%80%94%20but%20symptoms%20typically%20don't%20appear%20until%20it's%20more%20developed%20and%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eharder%20to%20treat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20found%20at%20more%20advanced%20stages%2C%20treatment%20options%20are%20more%20limited%2C%20and%20at%20stage%204%2C%20which%20is%20where%20the%20cancer%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprostate-cancer-cases-on-the-rise-as-screenings-decline-2020-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Espread%20from%20the%20prostate%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20body%2C%20%26quot%3Btreatment%20won't%20cure%20your%20cancer%2C%20but%20it%20can%20help%20keep%20it%20under%20control%20and%20manage%20any%20symptoms%2C%26quot%3B%20Chiara%20De%20Biase%2C%20%3Cspan%3Edirector%20of%20health%20services%2C%20Equity%2C%20and%20Improvement%20at%20%3C%2Fspan%3Ethe%20charity%20Prostate%20Cancer%20UK%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBiden's%20team%20has%20not%20shared%20what%20stage%20of%20cancer%20he%20has%20or%20his%20prognosis%2C%20but%20said%20it%20was%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fendocrine-disruptors-dangerous-chemicals-2019-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehormone%20sensitive%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20meaning%20it%20uses%20hormones%20to%20grow%20and%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20be%20managed%20with%20drugs%20that%20block%20hormones%20in%20the%20body.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fe7127a2-65b9-42e0-a52e-5ed4c392ad3e%5C%22%3EEasy%20to%20miss%20symptoms%20of%20prostate%20cancer%20include%20changes%20in%20how%20a%20person%20pees%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EChanges%20in%20urinary%20habits%20tend%20to%20be%20the%20earliest%20sign%20that%20a%20person%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprostate-cancer-early-signs-2018-11%23difficulty-peeing-is-an-early-sign-of-prostate-cancer-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprostate%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E.%20If%20the%20tumor%20grows%20near%20and%20presses%20against%20the%20tube%20we%20urinate%20through%20(the%20urethra)%20it%20can%20change%20the%20way%20the%20person%20pees.%20But%20early%20prostate%20cancer%20usually%20grows%20in%20a%20different%20part%20of%20the%20prostate%20away%20from%20the%20urethra%2C%20so%20it%20doesn't%20tend%20to%20cause%20symptoms%20until%20much%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChanges%20in%20how%20a%20person%20with%20prostate%20cancer%20pees%20can%20include%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EDifficulty%20starting%20to%20pee%20or%20emptying%20your%20bladder%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20weak%20flow%20when%20you%20pee%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20feeling%20that%20your%20bladder%20hasn't%20emptied%20properly%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDribbling%20urine%20after%20you%20finish%20urinating%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENeeding%20to%20pee%20more%20often%20than%20usual%2C%20especially%20at%20night%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20sudden%20need%20to%20pee%20or%20sometimes%20leaking%20pee%20before%20you%20get%20to%20the%20toilet.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20important%20to%20note%20that%20these%20changes%20can%20also%20be%20a%20sign%20of%20a%20common%20non-cancerous%20condition%20called%20enlarged%20prostate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ccc6fd45-7a2f-4661-a904-86c1dc9d2ea4%5C%22%3EIf%20prostate%20cancer%20spreads%2C%20other%20symptoms%20can%20include%3A%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EBack%20pain%2C%20hip%20pain%20or%20pelvis%20pain%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EProblems%20getting%20or%20keeping%20an%20erection%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBlood%20in%20the%20urine%20or%20semen%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EUnexplained%20weight%20loss%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWeakness%20or%20numbness%20in%20the%20legs%20or%20feet%2C%20or%20even%20loss%20of%20bladder%20or%20bowel%20control%2C%20from%20cancer%20in%20the%20spine%20pressing%20on%20the%20spinal%20cord%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d7c20f53-73a2-4463-ae0f-d9c6beb2e5dd%5C%22%3EMen%20are%20diagnosed%20with%20prostate%20cancer%20at%20the%20age%20of%2067%2C%20on%20average%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBiden%20is%2082.%20The%20ACS%20recommends%20that%20men%20with%20an%20average%20risk%20of%20prostate%20cancer%20consider%20getting%20screened%20at%20age%2050.%20The%20test%20involves%20taking%20a%20blood%20sample%20and%20checking%20for%20higher-than-normal%20prostate-specific%20antigen%20levels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20so%20important%20for%20men%20to%20know%20their%20own%20risk%2C%20and%20what%20they%20can%20choose%20to%20do%20about%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20De%20Biase%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjoe-biden-diagnosed-prostate-cancer-symptoms-miss-change-pee-2025-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1747653490000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F682b0eb8c6ad288d1481468c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjoe-biden-diagnosed-prostate-cancer-symptoms-miss-change-pee-2025-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Prostate%20cancer%20is%20the%