5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20aerial%20view%20of%20the%20Hull%20096%20ship%20at%20a%20port.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6819f4e7c6ad288d14801d6e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222122%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAustralian%20shipbuilder%20Incat%20launched%20Hull%20096%20from%20Hobart%2C%20Tasmania.%3Cp%3EIncat%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EIncat%20launched%20the%20world's%20largest%20electric%20ship%20%E2%80%94%20the%20biggest%20EV%20ever%20built%20%E2%80%94%20this%20month.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EElectric%20vessels%20are%20only%20suited%20to%20routes%20of%20less%20than%20200%20miles%2C%20Incat's%20founder%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDemand%20is%20rising%2C%20but%20scaling%20up%20production%20poses%20a%20major%20challenge%20for%20Incat%2C%20Robert%20Clifford%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EElectric%20shipping%20has%20reached%20a%20major%20milestone%2C%20but%20long-haul%20routes%20remain%20a%20distant%20dream.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20month%20Australian%20shipbuilder%20Incat%20launched%20Hull%20096%2C%20a%20427-foot%20fully%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworlds-largest-electric-ship-just-launched-first-of-its-kind-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eelectric%20ferry%3C%2Fa%3E%20built%20for%20South%20American%20operator%20Buquebus.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20vessel%2C%20now%20docked%20in%20Hobart%2C%20Tasmania%2C%20is%20the%20largest%20electric%20vehicle%20ever%20built.%20It%20is%20designed%20to%20carry%202%2C100%20passengers%20and%20225%20vehicles%20across%20the%20R%C3%ADo%20de%20la%20Plata%20between%20Buenos%20Aires%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcountries-i-loved-that-should-be-more-popular-frequent-traveler-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EUruguay%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20is%20powered%20by%20about%20275%20tons%20of%20batteries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIncat's%20chairman%20and%20founder%2C%20Robert%20Clifford%2C%20said%20ships%20like%20Hull%20096%20are%20still%20best%20suited%20for%20short%20distances%20%E2%80%94%20not%20the%20open%20ocean.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cda0b86a-b5e0-425d-9bcc-019ae12236d5%5C%22%3EDensity%20dilemma%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20not%20the%20slightest%20doubt%20that%20under%2050%20miles%2C%20electric%20will%20be%20virtually%20100%25%2C%26quot%3B%20Clifford%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20you're%20talking%20200%20miles%2C%20it%20might%20only%20be%2050%25.%20Over%20that%2C%20it'd%20be%20zero%20at%20the%20moment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20the%20main%20issue%20was%20the%20limited%20energy%20density%20of%20batteries%2C%20which%20still%20don't%20offer%20the%20same%20storage%20capacity%20per%20weight%20and%20volume%20as%20fossil%20fuels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20why%20Incat%20is%20focusing%20on%20ferries%20for%20high-density%2C%20relatively%20short%20routes%20like%20those%20in%20the%20English%20Channel%20or%20the%20Baltic%20Sea%20instead%20of%20oceangoing%20ships.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20ferry%20boat%20builders%2C%26quot%3B%20Clifford%20said.%20%26quot%3BEven%20a%20very%20large%20ferry%20for%20most%20routes%20would%20not%20go%20over%20about%20160%20meters.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223806%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20aerial%20view%20of%20Incat's%20Hull%20096%20at%20a%20port.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6819ee9fc6ad288d14801d23%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222136%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFerry%20operator%20Buquebus%20commissioned%20Incat%20to%20build%20a%20vessel%20to%20run%20between%20Buenos%20Aires%20and%20Uruguay.%3Cp%3EIncat%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20Clifford%20believes%20Hull%20096%20marks%20a%20turning%20point%20for%20clean%20maritime%20transport.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20ship%20changes%20the%20game%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%20a%20press%20release%20earlier%20this%20month.%20%26quot%3BWe've%20been%20building%20world-leading%20vessels%20here%20in%20Tasmania%20for%20more%20than%20four%20decades%2C%20and%20Hull%20096%20is%20the%20most%20ambitious%2C%20most%20complex%2C%20and%20most%20important%20project%20we've%20ever%20delivered.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ferry%20boasts%20a%2040%20megawatt-hour%20battery%20%E2%80%94%20the%20largest%20installed%20on%20a%20ship%20%E2%80%94%20feeding%20eight%20waterjets%20designed%20by%20Finnish%20firm%20W%C3%A4rtsil%C3%A4.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20interior%2C%20which%20includes%20a%202%2C300-square-meter%20duty-free%20shopping%20deck%2C%20is%20set%20to%20be%20completed%20this%20year%20ahead%20of%20trials%20on%20Tasmania's%20Derwent%20River.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuquebus%20had%20originally%20commissioned%20Hull%20096%20as%20a%20liquid%20natural%20gas-powered%20ferry%2C%20but%20Incat%20convinced%20the%20company%20to%20go%20electric.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20while%20Clifford%20is%20bullish%20on%20the%20tech%2C%20he%20said%20real-world%20adoption%20depends%20on%20port%20infrastructure%20and%20customer%20readiness.%20%26quot%3BWe%20simply%20need%20the%20shipowner%20to%20do%20their%20sums.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20there's%20been%20strong%20demand%20since%20Hull%20096's%20launch%20and%20was%20in%20talks%20with%20a%20dozen%20%26quot%3Bserious%26quot%3B%20clients%20from%20Europe%20and%20South%20America.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20been%20in%20this%20entrepreneurial%20business%20for%2030-odd%20years%2C%20and%20we've%20never%20had%20so%20many%20serious%20potential%20orders%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223ea8ac5d-9baf-4a94-97ca-845582498b55%5C%22%3EGrowth%20challenge%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20scaling%20production%20in%20Tasmania%20is%20a%20massive%20leap.%20%26quot%3BWe've%20been%20building%20one%20or%20two%20boats%20a%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20Clifford%20said.%20%26quot%3BBuilding%20four%20or%20more%20large%20boats%20a%20year%20is%20a%20massive%20increase%20in%20the%20size%20of%20the%20company%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20would%20require%20going%20from%20500%20to%203%2C000%20staff%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20today's%20challenge%20%E2%80%94%20how%20do%20we%20transition%20to%20a%20significant%20shipbuilder%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20Tasmania%20becomes%20a%20global%20hub%20for%20electric%20shipbuilding%20remains%20to%20be%20seen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWilliam%20%26quot%3BBoeing%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20had%20a%20small%20shipyard%20in%20Seattle%2C%26quot%3B%20Clifford%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20probably%20wasn't%20the%20best%20place%20in%20the%20world%20to%20start%20building%20airplanes.%20But%20he%20did%2C%20and%20then%20he%20sold%20100%20to%20the%20US%20Army.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20suddenly%20went%20from%20a%20small%20boat%20builder%20to%20a%20leading%20aircraft%20manufacturer%20all%20in%20a%20period%20of%20about%20a%20year%20or%20two.%20That%20sort%20of%20challenge%20is%20ahead%20of%20us.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felectric-ships-incat-ferry-tasmania-challenges-batteries-oceans-2025-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1747646704000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6825d71068a29290080162ed%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felectric-ships-incat-ferry-tasmania-challenges-batteries-oceans-2025-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22This%20month's%20launch%20of%20Hull%20096%20shows%20that%20ferries%20are%20going%20electric%20too%2C%20although%20challenges%20remain%2C%20Incat%20founder%20Robert%20Clifford%20tells%20BI.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tspirlet%40insider.com%20(Thibault%20Spirlet)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A51%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felectric-ships-incat-ferry-tasmania-challenges-batteries-oceans-2025-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Here's%20how%2